Having tried domino's in several countries in Europe, I previously had good experiences with this company as the food tasted nice as well as being decent value. However, here in New Orleans, the pizza smelt almost as bad as it tasted with the cheese leaving a disappointing taste and aftertaste while the tomato sauce gave the feeling of colouring, flavouring and preservatives left in a can for 15 years. It's a pity because the service was actually good where we received our delivery quite swiftly, maybe it's because we were the only people silly enough to order here. If you're visiting from abroad and want to see what Domino's is like here... don't!
